answers.body_markdown:
So first based on your given attempt it could **not** work because those given parameters (defined via `mvn Dclassifier=sources dependency:copy -Dartifact=log4j:log4j:1.2.8`) simply do not exist. Please check the documentation for the [goal `copy`][1].

What you can do is setting up a simply pom file which looks like this:

&lt;!-- language:language-xml --&gt;

    &lt;project
        xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0&quot;
        xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;
        xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd&quot;&gt;
    
      &lt;modelVersion&gt;4.0.0&lt;/modelVersion&gt;
    
      &lt;groupId&gt;com.soebes.so.example.download&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;example-download&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;1.0-SNAPSHOT&lt;/version&gt;
    
    
      &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;pluginManagement&gt;
          &lt;plugins&gt;
            .
            &lt;plugin&gt;
              &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
              &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
              &lt;version&gt;3.6.1&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
            ..
          &lt;/plugins&gt;
        &lt;/pluginManagement&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
          &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;executions&gt;
              &lt;execution&gt;
                &lt;id&gt;copy&lt;/id&gt;
                &lt;phase&gt;none&lt;/phase&gt;
                &lt;goals&gt;
                  &lt;goal&gt;copy&lt;/goal&gt;
                &lt;/goals&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                  &lt;artifactItems&gt;
                    &lt;artifactItem&gt;
                      &lt;groupId&gt;${groupId}&lt;/groupId&gt;
                      &lt;artifactId&gt;${artifactId}&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                      &lt;version&gt;${version}&lt;/version&gt;
                      &lt;classifier&gt;sources&lt;/classifier&gt;
                      &lt;outputDirectory&gt;${project.build.directory}&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
                    &lt;/artifactItem&gt;
                  &lt;/artifactItems&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
              &lt;/execution&gt;
            &lt;/executions&gt;
          &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
      &lt;/build&gt;
    &lt;/project&gt;


By using the above you could now call the command line like this:


    mvn dependency:copy@copy  -DgroupId=log4j -DartifactId=log4j -Dversion=1.2.9

That will download the given artifact and store into the location defined by `&lt;outputDirectory&gt;${project.build.directory}&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;` 


  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-dependency-plugin/copy-mojo.html

