is a really bad idea.

Swing is an event driven environment, that is, something happens and you respond to it (the `ActionListener` is an example of this).  

Swing is also single threaded (and not thread safe) so your `while-loop` runs the risk of blocking the Event Dispatching Thread which would cause your UI to be unresponsive.  

Having said that, the `break` statement will cause the loop to exit on the first iteration anyway.

In general, it&#39;s just a bad idea.

