See: 

* [Painting in AWT and Swing](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/painting.html)
* [Performing Custom Painting](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/painting/index.html)

for more details.

I&#39;d then make use of the `Shape`s API which provides a lot of additional support including simplified painting and hit box detection.

